  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rehabilitation of 100 damaged houses in Huseiniya  upgrading 200 unfinished private apartments in Ashrafiet Sahnaya</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Syria Trust will facilitate the return of families to their homes in Husseiniya through re-habilitation of 100 segregated damaged houses. This will be done on the premise that the selected families can provide legal documentation proving ownership of their homes. These houses will accommodate 2 or more related families.

Upgrading 200 unfinished private apartments  in Ashrafiet Sahnaya. The project will be the improvement of the living standards of those families by finishing the work inside the apartments with the basic needs such as doors, windows, clean water and sanitary work.
This project should help those families be protected from the hard winter conditions in rural Damascus. The 200 apartments are a part of different buildings, therefore some will fit 2 or 3 one family.</narrative>
  </description>
